SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260413T005344Z
DTSTART:20260413T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, April 13\, 2026\, 11am - 5pm\n\nTrained volunteers wil
	l be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.\n\nLo
	cation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Level 5 - Mixing Chamber
	 Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nD
	etailed Description: Drop-in tax help is offered on a first-come\, first-s
	erved basis.\, This service is free and available to individuals only.\, T
	he free service is not available for business tax returns.\, To receive ta
	x help\, bring the following documents:\,\n\nRequired Documents:\n\nPhoto 
	identification\, Social Security cards or Individual Taxpayer Identificati
	on Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyone listed on the tax return\, Proof of inc
	ome\, for example\, W2s and 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Officia
	l documents on Social Security Administration letterhead\, Medicare card \
	\(if Social Security number is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to prov
	ide information about health care coverage for each person on the return\,
	\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year's tax return\, if available\, Bank account a
	nd routing numbers for direct deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer
	 print-outs of any of these documents will be accepted.\, Due to federal b
	udget cuts the IRS is unable to provide the Library with certain tax forms
	 and instruction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available online at\n\nwww
	.irs.gov. \, You may make free black-and-white prints of the forms from Li
	brary computers:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nUnited W
	ay of King County .\n\nEvent Logistics: United Way Tax Help locations serv
	e anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025 \\(or less than $96\,000 fo
	r non-single filers\\).\, For eligibility details\, contact United Way at 
	206-461-3700.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nA
	sk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accom
	modations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontac
	tLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.\,
	 All Library programs are free and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://seatod
	ay.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-04-13T00\n\nFr
	om SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/20
	26-04-13T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
