BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:SpIRpBUiUWaCOXRjm-ez6
SUMMARY:Living with Conviction: Sentenced to Debt for Life in Washington St
	ate Exhibit
DTSTAMP:20260413T005345Z
DTSTART:20260418T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Saturday\, April 18\, 2026\, 10am - 6pm\n\nThis exhibitconfront
	s how Washington courts have been sentencing people not only to prison but
	 also to a lifetime of debt.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom 
	Location: Level 8 - Gallery\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not 
	required.\n\nDetailed Description: "Living with Conviction: Sentenced to D
	ebt for Life in Washington State" confronts how Washington courts have bee
	n sentencing people not only to prison but also to a lifetime of debt. The
	 project leverages multimedia storytelling and community conversations to 
	raise awareness about and advocate for an end to crippling court-imposed c
	osts\, fees\, fines\, and restitution\, commonly referred to as Legal Fina
	ncial Obligations\, or LFOs. "Living with Conviction: Sentenced to Debt fo
	r Life in Washington State\," goes beyond polarizing headlines and statist
	ics\, shining a light on this injustice by sharing stories of our common h
	umanity.\, Thanks to our partner\n\nLiving with Conviction .\, Thanks to o
	ur sponsor\n\nThe Seattle Public Library Foundation .\n\nEvent Logistics: 
	The gallery is open during Central Libray's open hours.\, Living with Conv
	iction is a 501\\(c\\)\\(3\\) nonprofit that works to secure economic and 
	racial justice with and by marginalized communities\, especially formerly 
	incarcerated\, through community-driven research\, storytelling\, and lega
	l empowerment strategies.\, This exhibit runs through July 26\, 2026\, Lea
	rn more about\n\nExhibits .\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about thi
	s event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can
	 provide accommodations for people with disabilities at Library events. Pl
	ease\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request acc
	ommodations.\, All Library programs are free and open to the public.\n\nht
	tps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/living-with-conviction-sentenc
	ed-to-debt-for-life-in-washington-state-exhibit/18572479/2026-04-18T00\n\n
	From SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/living-with-conviction-se
	ntenced-to-debt-for-life-in-washington-state-exhibit/18572479/2026-04-18T0
	0
LOCATION:Northwest Worklofts (Commons)\, 107 West Denny Way\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
